{"id":29513,"title":"[Do patients increase smoking during alcohol withdrawal?].","abstract":"Alcoholics are very often addicted to tobacco. However, a study carried out in an intersectorial addictology centre with hospitalised patients receiving first-line treatment for alcohol withdrawal highlights a decrease in this consumption, notably for people benefiting from specific care management.","date":"2014-03-24","categories":"Chemically-Induced Disorders","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24654336","annotations":[{"name":"Alcohol","weight":0.743484,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcohol"},{"name":"Alcohol withdrawal syndrome","weight":0.723473,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcohol_withdrawal_syndrome"},{"name":"Tobacco","weight":0.700688,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tobacco"},{"name":"Smoking","weight":0.697734,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smoking"},{"name":"Withdrawal","weight":0.684152,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Withdrawal"},{"name":"Alcoholism","weight":0.681913,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcoholism"},{"name":"Substance dependence","weight":0.630946,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Substance_dependence"},{"name":"Tuberculosis","weight":0.401749,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuberculosis"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.335087,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Management","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Management"}]}
